cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.RO, cs.PL

The paper proposes a method for learning high level functional programs to represent abstract models from observed data traces. This involves system identification of dynamical systems, explaining the behavior of a DQN agent, and learning by demonstration in a human-robot interaction scenario. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning) as the paper focuses on learning from data. The paper also involves reasoning and explaining the behavior of systems, which suggests that it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Additionally, the paper involves learning by demonstration in a human-robot interaction scenario, which suggests that it could belong to cs.RO (Robotics). Finally, the paper proposes an architecture for program induction, which suggests that it could belong to cs.PL (Programming Languages).
